HEADWORD: Errhine
<hw>Er"rhine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/ in +
<?/, <?/, nose: cf. F. <ets>errhin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A medicine designed to be snuffed up the nose, to promote
discharges of mucus; a sternutatory.</def> <au>Coxe.</au> --
<def2><pos>a.</pos> <def>Causing or increasing secretion of nasal
mucus.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erroneous</ent>⟦br⟧
